%META:TOPICPARENT{name="WebHome"}%
---+ Energy Thresholds

%TOC%

The right-side panel carries one slider tab per object class. A hit, cluster
or track is drawn only when its energy (or p_T) lies inside the tab's
=[min, max]= window. The sliders do not modify the underlying event — they
are display-time filters.

<img src="images/threshold-panel.png" alt="Threshold panel layout" width="260" />

---++ Tabs

| *Tab*     | *Object*              | *Units* | *Default floor* | *Default ceiling*    |
| TILE      | TileCal cell          | GeV     | 0               | auto (P97 of event)  |
| LAr       | LAr EM cell           | GeV     | 0               | auto (P97)           |
| FCAL      | LAr FCAL cell         | GeV     | 0               | auto (P97)           |
| HEC       | LAr HEC cell          | GeV     | 0               | auto (P97)           |
| Track     | Reconstructed track   | GeV     | 0.5             | –                    |
| Cluster   | Topological cluster   | GeV     | 0.5             | –                    |

The Cluster tab has its own =Cluster Threshold= on/off switch: when off, all
clusters render regardless of E_T.

---++ P97 auto-scaling

By default the ceiling of every calorimeter tab is set to the 97th
percentile of that sub-detector's cell energies for the current event. The
palette therefore spans the bulk of the deposits rather than being
dominated by a single high-energy cell.

The read-out above each slider shows the current ceiling (e.g. =2.00 GeV=).
Double-click the slider to re-sample P97 if the event has just changed;
pick a numeric value in the text input to lock an absolute ceiling.

---++ Typed input

Every tab exposes a text field below the slider. Accepted formats:

<verbatim>
200            -> 200 MeV (default unit)
200 MeV        -> 200 MeV
1.5 GeV        -> 1 500 MeV
2e3            -> 2 000 MeV
</verbatim>

Invalid input is silently ignored and the slider stays put.

---++ Palette behaviour

Each sub-detector has a per-tab cold-to-hot gradient (see
[[Overview][Overview]] for the accent colours). Within =[min, max]=:

   * A hit at =min= renders with the coldest colour.
   * A hit at =max= renders with the hottest colour.
   * Hits below =min= are culled.
   * Hits above =max= saturate at the hottest colour.

---++ Recipes

| *Goal*                                   | *Action*                                        |
| Hide sub-MIP noise                       | Raise TILE / LAr floor to a few hundred MeV     |
| Show only the shower core                | Raise floors on TILE and LAr simultaneously     |
| Keep the scale fixed across events       | Lock each ceiling with a typed value            |
| Isolate a single high-p_T track          | Raise Track floor to the desired p_T            |
| Compare two events in the same capture   | Same typed ceilings on both captures            |

---++ Interaction with geometry

Thresholds never hide cells themselves, only their energy bars. To hide a
whole sub-detector, use the [[UserInterface][Detector Layers panel]].

